# CLAUDE.local.md — Developer Machine Setup

This file is a template. Copy it to `CLAUDE.local.md` (which is gitignored) and fill in
the values for your environment. Do NOT commit `CLAUDE.local.md` — it contains paths and
settings that are specific to your machine and will break other developers' setups.

---

## Git binary

If `git` is already in your system PATH (standard on Mac, Linux, and most Windows installs),
you can run git commands directly and skip this section.

If git is NOT in your PATH (common when using GitHub Desktop on Windows without a standalone
Git install), set the path to the git executable before running any git commands in PowerShell:

```powershell
$git = "<absolute-path-to-git.exe>"
& $git <command>
```

### Where to find git.exe on Windows

| Setup | Typical path |
|---|---|
| Standalone Git install | `C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe` |
| GitHub Desktop (Windows) | `C:\Users\<YourUsername>\AppData\Local\GitHubDesktop\app-<version>\resources\app\git\cmd\git.exe` |
| Scoop | `C:\Users\<YourUsername>\scoop\apps\git\current\bin\git.exe` |
| Winget / Microsoft Store Git | `C:\Program Files\Git\cmd\git.exe` |

To find it yourself, run this in PowerShell:
```powershell
Get-ChildItem "C:\Users\$env:USERNAME\AppData\Local\GitHubDesktop" -Recurse -Filter "git.exe" | Select-Object -First 1 FullName
```

